    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can’t handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>and <strong>wholewheat</strong> <strong>tortiglioni </strong>to the pot with the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong></p><p>Add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and 550m<span class=\"text-purple\">l [700ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[925ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Top the tortiglioni with your <strong>Greek cheese</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cover with the lid and put the dish in the oven for an initial 15 min</p>",
